s:1266:"<p dir="ltr" style="text-align:left;"></p><p style="text-align:justify;">The course on smart contract background is designed to provide users with a comprehensive understanding of smart contracts, including their history, use cases, and technical architecture.</p><p style="text-align:justify;">Users will start by learning about the history of smart contracts and how they have evolved over time. From there, the course will cover the technical underpinnings of smart contracts, including how they are coded, executed, and stored on a blockchain.</p><p style="text-align:justify;">The course will also explore the various use cases for smart contracts across industries, including finance, supply chain management, and real estate. Users will learn how smart contracts are being used to streamline processes, reduce costs, and increase transparency in these industries.</p><p style="text-align:justify;">By the end of the course, users will have a solid understanding of the role that smart contracts play in the blockchain ecosystem and how they are being used to revolutionize industries. This knowledge will serve as a foundation for the second course, which will focus specifically on smart contract security.</p><p style="text-align:justify;"><br /></p><p></p>";